  "text": "It has earlier been observed that, when applied to domains, the posterior distribution inferred by MrBayes typically is too flat to allow proper conclusions [CITATION_1] and we show that DomainDLRS solves this problem. DomainDLRS clade support values display a distribution much more centered around higher support values compared to MrBayesMPR.",
